As of the census of 2010, 264 people lived in the town, a decrease of 10.81% since 2000 (32 people). The [[Race (United States Census)|racial makeup]] of the town was 62.80% White, 32.65% African American, 3.41% from other races, and 1.14% from two or more races. Hispanics or Latinos of any race were 15.91% of the population. In 2014, the population was estimated to be 258.{{clear left}}

